    "what_description": "Mariscus globosus is a species of flowering plant in the family Cyperaceae. It is a perennial, monocotyledonous plant with a short rhizome, producing several stems from a single point of origin, each reaching up to 1 meter in height. Leaves are linear, flat, and glabrous, measuring up to 10 cm in length, and are arranged in a two-ranked, distichous pattern. The inflorescence is a spike-like raceme, bearing small, unisexual flowers, with the female flowers occurring in the lower part of the spike and the male flowers in the upper part. The spike is surrounded by a white or pale yellowish bract, and the plant typically flowers from April to May.",
