    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Mariscus globosus are tea, infusion, tincture, salve, and decoction. Tea and infusion are prepared by steeping the leaves in hot water to treat fever, rheumatism, and digestive issues due to its anti-inflammatory and antibacterial properties. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract used to treat respiratory issues like bronchitis and asthma due to its expectorant properties. Salve is a topical preparation used to treat wounds, skin infections, and eczema due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties. Decoction is a boiling liquid extract used to treat gastrointestinal issues like diarrhea and dysentery due to its purgative and anti-inflammatory properties.",
